methods.initialize:
Initialize this operation.

:param usePrev: (boolean) - data from the previous cycle should be used (otherwise use this cycle)
:param beforeClock: (long) - the clock value that we captured before the function began; the function can use this
        value to bail out early if it notices something has gone wrong.
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.QueryTable.Operation.Result<io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.QueryTable>) the result table / listener if successful, null if it should be retried.
methods.transform:
Transform an outer (reversed) RowSet to the inner (unreversed) RowSet, or vice versa.

*Overload 1*  
  :param rowSetToTransform: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - the outer RowSet
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.WritableRowSet) the corresponding inner RowSet
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param outerIndex: (long) - the outer RowSet
  :return: (long) the corresponding inner RowSet
methods.transformPrev:
Transform an outer (reversed) RowSet to the inner (unreversed) RowSet as of the previous cycle, or vice versa.

*Overload 1*  
  :param outerRowSet: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - the outer RowSet
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.WritableRowSet) the corresponding inner RowSet
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param outerIndex: (long) - the outer RowSet
  :return: (long) the corresponding inner RowSet
